.TH TAUDIT 1 "2026-04-24" "taudit 0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
taudit \- pipeline authority scanner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B taudit
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B taudit
builds a directed authority graph from CI/CD pipeline YAML and walks it looking for security issues: secrets crossing trust boundaries, over-privileged identities, unpinned actions, credentials persisted to disk, and more.
.PP
Supported platforms: GitHub Actions (default), Azure DevOps.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS taudit scan \fIpath...\fR
Scan one or more pipeline files or directories for authority findings.
.TP
.B path
One or more paths to pipeline YAML files or directories. Use
.B \-
to read from stdin.
.TP
.B \-\-platform \fIplatform\fR
CI/CD platform to parse. One of
.BR github\-actions " (default) or " azure\-devops .
.TP
.B \-\-format \fIfmt\fR
Output format. One of
.BR terminal " (default), " json ", " sarif ", " cloudevents .
.TP
.B \-\-max\-hops \fIn\fR
Maximum BFS depth for propagation analysis (default: 4).
.TP
.B \-\-severity\-threshold \fIlevel\fR
Minimum severity to produce a non-zero exit code. Findings below this level still appear in the report.
Values:
.BR critical ", " high ", " medium ", " low ", " info .
.TP
.B \-\-ignore\-file \fIpath\fR
Path to a
.I .tauditignore
file. Defaults to
.I .tauditignore
in the working directory if present.
.TP
.B \-\-exclude \fIglob\fR
Glob pattern to exclude from scanning. May be specified multiple times.
.TP
.B \-\-baseline \fIpath\fR
Path to a JSON report from a prior scan. Findings whose (category, message) pair appears in the baseline are suppressed.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Summary-only output: print finding counts per file and a grand total instead of full per-finding details.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Show node metadata (kind, trust zone, permissions) for each node in a finding's propagation path.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI color codes in terminal output. Also honored via the
.B NO_COLOR
environment variable (any value disables color). Color is on by default \[em] CI log viewers (GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps) render ANSI from piped stdout.
.TP
.B \-\-telemetry\-dir \fIpath\fR
Directory to write telemetry events (JSONL). Default:
.BR $TAUDIT_TELEMETRY_DIR " or " $XDG_STATE_HOME/taudit/telemetry " or " $HOME/.local/state/taudit/telemetry .
If none can be resolved, telemetry is silently skipped.
.TP
.B \-\-receipt\-dir \fIpath\fR
Directory to write scan receipts (JSON). Default:
.BR $TAUDIT_RECEIPT_DIR " or " $XDG_DATA_HOME/taudit/receipts " or " $HOME/.local/share/taudit/receipts .
.TP
.B \-\-log\-dir \fIpath\fR
Directory to write plain-text logs. Default:
.BR $TAUDIT_LOG_DIR " or " $XDG_STATE_HOME/taudit/logs " or " $HOME/.local/state/taudit/logs .
.SS taudit map \fIpath...\fR
Print a tabular authority map showing which steps access which secrets and identities.
.TP
.B \-\-platform \fIplatform\fR
CI/CD platform to parse (same values as
.BR scan ).
.SS taudit diff \fIbefore\fR \fIafter\fR
Compare findings between two pipeline revisions.
.TP
.B \-\-format \fIfmt\fR
Output format. One of
.BR terminal " (default), " json .
.TP
.B \-\-platform \fIplatform\fR
CI/CD platform to parse.
.SS taudit completions \fIshell\fR
Print shell completions to stdout.
Values:
.BR bash ", " zsh ", " fish ", " powershell ", " elvish .
.SS taudit emit\-spec \fItarget\fR
Emit a CellOS execution-cell JSON spec that runs
.B taudit scan
in an isolation runtime.
.SS taudit version
Print the taudit version string.
.SH FINDING CATEGORIES
.TP
.B authority_propagation
Secret or identity propagated to a step in a lower trust zone. Severity: Critical (untrusted sink), High (SHA-pinned sink), Medium (SHA-pinned + constrained identity).
.TP
.B over_privileged_identity
Identity with broader scope than needed. Severity: High (broad), Medium (unknown).
.TP
.B unpinned_action
Third-party action or image not pinned to a SHA digest. Severity: Medium.
.TP
.B untrusted_with_authority
Untrusted step has direct access to a secret or identity. Severity: Critical. If the secret is passed via a Terraform
.B \-var
flag, the message notes log exposure risk and recommends
.B TF_VAR_*
env vars instead.
.TP
.B artifact_boundary_crossing
Artifact from a privileged step consumed across a trust boundary. Severity: High.
.TP
.B floating_image
Container image without a Docker digest pin. Severity: Medium.
.TP
.B long_lived_credential
Secret name matches static credential patterns (API keys, passwords, signing keys). Severity: Low.
.TP
.B persisted_credential
Checkout step with
.B persistCredentials: true
writes the access token to
.I .git/config
on disk, making it accessible to all subsequent steps. Severity: High.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
When set to any value, disables ANSI color output. Takes precedence over
.BR \-\-no\-color .
See
.I https://no-color.org/
for the specification.
.TP
.B TAUDIT_TELEMETRY_DIR
Override the telemetry directory. Takes precedence over XDG defaults.
.TP
.B TAUDIT_RECEIPT_DIR
Override the receipt directory.
.TP
.B TAUDIT_LOG_DIR
Override the log directory. Log files are always written as plain text regardless of color settings.
.TP
.B XDG_STATE_HOME
Used to resolve telemetry and log directories when
.B TAUDIT_TELEMETRY_DIR
and
.B TAUDIT_LOG_DIR
are not set.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Used to resolve the receipt directory when
.B TAUDIT_RECEIPT_DIR
is not set.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
No actionable findings (or all findings are below
.BR \-\-severity\-threshold ).
.TP
.B 1
One or more findings meet or exceed the severity threshold.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Scan all GitHub Actions workflows
taudit scan .github/workflows/

# Scan an Azure DevOps pipeline
taudit scan .pipelines/azure-pipelines.yml --platform azure-devops

# Fail only on critical findings; SARIF output for code scanning
taudit scan .github/workflows/ --format sarif --severity-threshold critical

# Suppress previously accepted findings
taudit scan . --baseline taudit-baseline.json

# Compare two revisions
taudit diff before.yml after.yml

# Force plain output (no color)
NO_COLOR=1 taudit scan .github/workflows/
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
Project home: https://github.com/0ryant/taudit
.PP
Bug reports: https://github.com/0ryant/taudit/issues
